The folder `LAMMPS/ElConst/` input:
- the MLIP settings file (mlip.ini)
- the additional files (in.elastic, displace.mod, init.mod, and potential.mod) needed to 
calculate the elastic constants using the LAMMPS code with MTPs
- the file read-ElasticConstants-create-file.py needed to retrieve the constants C11, C12, and C44
- the fitted MTP (pot.mtp, should be copied to the folder `LAMMPS/ElConst/`)
- the equilibrium configuration (relaxed.cfg, should be copied to the folder `LAMMPS/ElConst/`)

The folder `LAMMPS` input:
- the shell script elastic-constants.sh calculates the elastic constants C11, C12, and C44
